<p><b>Hop</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Lisp_(programming_language)" title="Lisp (programming language)">Lisp</a>-like <a href="/wiki/Programming_language" title="Programming language">programming language</a> by <a href="/w/index.php?title=Manuel_Serrano&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Manuel Serrano (page does not exist)">Manuel Serrano</a> for <a href="/wiki/Web_2.0" title="Web 2.0">web 2.0</a> and also the name of the <a href="/wiki/Web_broker" class="mw-redirect" title="Web broker">web broker</a> (<a href="/wiki/Web_server" title="Web server">server</a> and <a href="/wiki/Web_proxy" class="mw-redirect" title="Web proxy">proxy</a>) that implements this language. It is written in <a href="/wiki/Bigloo" title="Bigloo">Bigloo</a> <a href="/wiki/Scheme_(programming_language)" title="Scheme (programming language)">Scheme</a>. It is a project funded by <a href="/wiki/INRIA" class="mw-redirect" title="INRIA">INRIA</a>.</p>
<p></p>
