<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Issues">Issues</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Hop_(software)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Issues">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Given its recent introduction, Hop currently exhibits a number of weaknesses.</p>
<ul>
<li>Security is weak. It is an area of active research<sup id="cite_ref-youtube_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-youtube-2">[2]</a></sup></li>
<li>Network failures are currently handled through manually coded time-out and exception routines. This approach is labor-intensive and relatively unreliable.<sup id="cite_ref-youtube_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-youtube-2">[2]</a></sup></li>
</ul>
